All commercial flights have ceased operation to/from Panama until at least 22 June 2020. There are currently no commercial options available to return to the UK from Panama, but some special flights are currently operating (see below).
If you cannot leave Panama at this time, see information on staying in Panama during coronavirus.
This travel advice will be updated when further departure options become available. Sign up for travel advice email alerts and follow the British Embassy on Twitter and Facebook.
Flight Update
Copa Airlines
Copa Airlines will be running special flights (flight numbers CM4060 and CM4070) on 28 May and 29 May departing from Panama City, Tocumen International Airport to Mexico City, Mexico and a special flight (flight number not yet available) on 30 May departing from Panama City, Tocumen International Airport to Miami, Florida, USA. Please book your flights on the Copa website or by calling +507 217-2672.
There are onward flights to the USA, Canada, France and the Netherlands from Mexico. There are onward flights to London Heathrow Airport from Miami International Airport. You should coordinate your onward travel to the UK accordingly. Check travel advice for any country you intend to transit or enter before booking any flights.
Spirit Airlines
Spirit Airlines will be running special flights (flight numbers NK 6511) on 3 June and 10 June departing from Panama City, Tocumen International Airport to Fort Lauderdale, Florida, USA.
Please use the following link to make your booking
There are onward flights to London Heathrow Airport from Miami International Airport. You should coordinate your onward connection to the UK accordingly.
United Airlines
United Airlines will be running special flights (flights number UA 3014 and UA 2417) on May 27 and June 3, departing from Panama City, Tocumen International Airport, to Houston, Texas, USA.
Passengers should note that in order to avoid the mandatory 14 days quarantine imposed by the state of Texas they will need to show that they have an onward booking to leave Houston within 4 hours of arrival. There are no direct flights from Houston to the UK and as such, it would be necessary for passengers to have booked an onward flight via another hub such as Miami.
Please use the following link to make your booking
Passengers with appropriate passport / visa permit or with a valid ESTA are qualified for this flight as long as they have been outside one of the designated areas (UK, Republic of Ireland, the Schengen Zone, Iran or China) for more than 14 days. British Nationals that have been outside one the designated areas away from UK/EU, China and Iran for 14 days can apply for an ESTA.
Please apply using the following link if you need a Visa waiver for the US
Passengers are responsible for coordinating travel to the airport. We are aware that transportation is restricted and you may have to book a private driver or taxi. We can facilitate a letter in Spanish and English for the driver that may assist with checkpoints to and from airport. Please email us your flight confirmation along with the following details: the driver’s full name; identification number (cedula), license plate number and make and model of the vehicle, and the names of British Nationals traveling with you.
We are monitoring the situation for further departures from Panama but these are likely to be limited until the air embargo is lifted (currently scheduled for 22nd June)
If local authorities need confirmation that you are in transit to the airport, please call +507-297-6550 for assistance.
Transport to the airport for this flight
Taxis, Cabify and InDriver continue to operate, as do the two transport options below. Others may be available. You should book in advance and inform the British Embassy of your arrangements, as below:
